trans-unit.source: Barrier: Ensures multiple threads will wait for each other to reach a point in the program, before continuing execution all together.

trans-unit.source: Box<T>, casually referred to as a 'box', provides the simplest form of heap allocation in Rust. Boxes provide ownership for this allocation, and drop their contents when they go out of scope. Boxes also ensure that they never allocate more than isize::MAX bytes.
